 -->\n<figure class=\"gb-block-image gb-block-image-a9c7d256\"><img class=\"gb-image gb-image-a9c7d256\" src=\"{{pushpull.home_url}}/app/uploads/LOGO_NARIES-1.png\" alt=\"\" title=\"LOGO_NARIES\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:generateblocks/image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column {\"width\":\"66.66%\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\"><!-- wp:generateblocks/headline {\"uniqueId\":\"ddc4faea\",\"element\":\"p\",\"blockVersion\":3} -->\n<p class=\"gb-headline gb-headline-ddc4faea gb-headline-text\">[go_link src=\"partners\" url=\"https://naries.ch/\"]NARIES[/go_link] is a nonprofit association recognized as serving the public interest. It was founded out of a deep passion for nature by two twin sisters from Geneva, both field biologists specializing in herpetology (amphibians and reptiles). Based in Geneva, NARIES aims to promote biodiversity conservation, primarily in Switzerland but also in neighboring France. Today, we believe it is our duty, as humans, to acknowledge the damage our society has caused to the environment and to take action to remedy it as much as possible. Discover, Share, Inform, Raise Awareness, and Act to Protect—these are the guiding principles of NARIES.</p>\n<!-- /wp:generateblocks/headline --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n<!-- /wp:generateblocks/container -->\n\n<!-- wp:generateblocks/container {\"uniqueId\":\"8c1df8b1\",\"isGrid\":true,\"gridId\":\"532f4855\",\"isDynamic\":true,\"blockVersion\":4,\"sizing\":{\"width\":\"50%\",\"widthMobile\":\"100%\"}} -->\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column {\"width\":\"33.33%\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\"><!-- wp:generateblocks/image {\"uniqueId\":\"d7bca24d\",\"mediaId\":4636,\"openInNewWindow\":true,\"relNoFollow\":true,\"relSponsored\":true,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"blockVersion\":2} -->\n<figure class=\"gb-block-image gb-block-image-d7bca24d\"><img class=\"gb-image gb-imag